# ==========================================================================
# .gitignore for the ElectroSim-DunnECASA Suite *public* repository.
#
# Goal: ship a clean, binary-only public repo. The .py source for the main
# app is NOT distributed here (see ../LICENSE). What this file blocks vs.
# allows:
#
#   * `*.py`            — block source Python files anywhere by default
#   * `web-demo/**`     — re-allow everything under web-demo/, including the
#                         loader stub (electrosim_app.py) and the
#                         requirements.txt the hosting platform needs.
#   * `release/build/`  — re-allow the build-reference folder; spec files
#                         and the build PS1 are deliberately published for
#                         transparency.
#   * `installer/Output/` — block the compiled installer.exe; it ships via
#                         GitHub Releases attachments, never via the repo.
# ==========================================================================

# --- Python source / build artifacts ---------------------------------------
*.py
*.pyc
__pycache__/
build/
dist/
venv/
.venv/
requirements*.txt

# --- Allowlist exceptions --------------------------------------------------
# Order matters: each `!` line re-includes files that an earlier blanket
# rule above had excluded.

# web-demo/ ships the loader stub + compiled bytecode + requirements.txt
!web-demo/
!web-demo/**

# build/ ships the PyInstaller spec files and the build orchestrator PS1
# for transparency about how the binaries are produced. The blanket `build/`
# rule above excludes any *local* PyInstaller build dir (named `build/`)
# at the repo root or anywhere else, but the release/build/ folder of this
# repo is intentionally tracked.
!build/
!build/**

# --- Installer build output ------------------------------------------------
# The compiled Setup-X.Y.exe is hundreds of MB and is uploaded as a GitHub
# Releases binary attachment — never committed to the repo.
# Anchored to the real location (this is the sole .gitignore now that the
# duplicate release/.gitignore has been removed).
release/installer/Output/
installer/Output/

# --- Local OS junk ---------------------------------------------------------
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
desktop.ini

# --- Editor scratch --------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
